cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a novel approach for multi-class semantic segmentation learning using fully convolutional networks and multiple instance learning. This involves optimizing the representation while disambiguating the pixel-image label assignment. The paper is likely to be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with semantic segmentation. It also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it uses multiple instance learning and optimization techniques. Additionally, it may fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves learning from weak image-level labels. It may also be categorized under natural language processing (cs.CL) as it involves semantic segmentation, which is a common task in NLP. Finally, it may fall under multimedia (cs.MM) as it involves processing visual data.
